h2 Directives

h2 &lt;fx-tracker&gt;
p Track animation values to determine if back or forward fx should be used

h4 Code Sample
textarea(style="width:100%;height:80px" wrap="off" readonly).
  &lt;fx-tracker #fx="FxTracker"&gt;&lt;/fx-tracker&gt;

h3 FxTracker properties
li FxTracker.id : 0|false|1|true
  ul
    li ack-angular-fx specific id to indicate fx transistion type
    li true == 'progressive animation'
    li 1 == 'progressive animation'
    li false == 'regressive animation'
    li 0 == 'regressive animation'

h3 fx-tracker bindings
li [value] : any
li [activatedRoute] : [ActivatedRoute](https://angular.io/api/router/ActivatedRoute)
li [orderArray]:any[]
  ul
    li back and foward fx can be determined by matching items in ordinal array instead of history tracking
li [(history)]:any[]
  ul
    li record of animation value history
li 
li [(index)]:number
  ul
    li current position in history